object.name: provider
object.customQuery:
SELECT n.GivenName as GivenName, s.SystemId as SystemId, s.Id as Id  
 from subrogation s
 join litigation l
on s.systemid=l.systemid
and l.parentid=s.id
 join litigationassociate la
on la.systemid=s.systemid
and la.parentid=l.id
 join provider p
on p.systemid=la.associateproviderref 
left join nameinfo n
on n.systemid=p.systemid
and n.nametypecd='ProviderName'
where associatetypecd='Subrogation Counsel'

object.name: reserveallocation
object.customQuery:
select distinct 
reserveallocation.RecoveryAmt as RecoveryAmt,
reserveallocation.SystemId as SystemId, 
claimanttransaction.SubrogationIdRef as SubrogationIdRef
from reserveallocation 
join featureallocation
on featureallocation.id = reserveallocation.parentid
and featureallocation.systemid = reserveallocation.SystemId
and featureallocation.CMMContainer = 'Claim'
join claimanttransaction
on claimanttransaction.id = featureallocation.ParentId
and claimanttransaction.SystemId = featureallocation.systemid
and claimanttransaction.CMMContainer = 'Claim'
and claimanttransaction.StatusCd = 'Active'
and SubrogationIdRef is not null
where reserveallocation.reservecd ='DeductibleRecovery'

object.customQuery:
select distinct 
             s.id as id, 
             s.subrogationproviderref as subrogationproviderref, 
             n.commercialname as lkp_subrogationprovidername
        from subrogation s
      join   provider p
          on s.subrogationproviderref = p.systemid 
      join   nameinfo n
          on p.systemid = n.systemid
         and p.CMMContainer = n.CMMContainer  
         and n.nametypecd = 'ProviderName'
